Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State has warned Nigerians of making right electoral choices in 2023. Makinde, in a post on his Twitter page, warned Nigerians to be reminded that their choices have consequences, hence should be prepared to make the right electoral choices. His tweet read: “As I take down my pinned tweet which showed my unequivocal stand against the #TwitterBan which lasted 222 days, I will like to remind us all that our choices have consequences. “With the 2023 elections around the corner, I hope we are prepared to make the right electoral choices.” In the past few days, some presidential aspirants have declared intention to contest for the presidency in 2023. Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, APC, informed President Muhammadu Buhari of his intention to run. Also, Dave Umahi, Chief Whip of the Senate and Dele Momodu have declared their intention to run for the presidency. Momodu boasted that he will defeat the APC if chosen as the PDP presidential candidate.